Thank you for your e-mail regarding entrance to Kindergarten in North Carolina. 



The North Carolina General Assembly voted to change the kindergarten cut off date in order to reduce the age and development gaps between incoming kindergarteners. Children with summer and fall birthdates were more likely to be held back from starting kindergarten than their older classmates, which created a disadvantage within the classroom. Older kindergarteners are more eager to learn, and are better able to pay attention.



