d properly! I was not going to subject my child to a life filled with severe complications because the people who are charged with taking care of him everyday are not doing just that. I also at that time asked for a 504 plan. I was told that he did not qualify for a 504 plan because he did not have any mental handicaps. I still insisted on having one. I also spoke with the principal and told him that he needed to correct this immediately. In January there was a collaborative meeting put in place, where Dr. Nolte informed the school nurse that he wanted a step-by-step care plan in place for JT... He wanted to know exactly who was doing what, and when, and what to do if that person was not available. My husband and I were pleased. We felt as if the school was really going to work with us on this. Jt was absent the entire month of January (with the exception of 4 days) because of the school not furnishing the revised care plan. Once I received it I reviewed it and made notes as to what was wrong with it. and spoke with the school nurse to explain to her that this "new" plan was the same thing that was already in place. And I would not sign it. The school social worker was then sent to my house to try and coerce me to sign it. My husband clearly stated that neither of us would sign that form. Yesterday the social worker returned to my house with a Waynesville Police officer with the forms again. I was at a private school enrolling JT at this time, because my husband and I had decided that we had had enough of trying to work with Haywood County Public School. Jt's A1C this month was down to an 8.1... I was able to prove my point that him being in a situation where they did not know how to take care of him, was detrimental to his health. Today, this morning, the school social worker again came to my house with letters from the school principal stating that I would be charged with Medical Neglect for not signing the care plan. And that by me keeping him out of school I would be charged with academic neglect for all 3 of my children. As of this morning at 10am, none of my children are enrolled in Haywood County Public Schools, because of this. This is insane that a principal would go to such great lengths to not take care of a child. All I have asked for is for them to treat him according to his doctors orders. and this is impossible for them to do. I asked for a 504 plan on 2 separate occasions, and I was denied. Parent to parent, I am asking you to please intervene and make this right. It is not fair for my children to have to leave all of their friends because of 1 school refusing to step up to the plate and do what they are required by federal law to do. Thank you so much for your time and prompt attention to this matter, Amber Fuller

