08 JT was refusing to go to school, stating that he "Hated school", he started to refuse to do his homework, he became very disrespectful to everyone, including teachers. I requested a log of his blood sugars at school and found that his blood sugar was completely out of control. I started at that time to request that additional trainings take place. I received no reply. In early December my husband and I experienced the death of a close friend... his funeral was scheduled for the same day as a field trip for JT. I was told by his teacher that if I could not go on the field trip to take care of him that he probably wouldn't be able to go. I was furious. I immediately called the principal stating that he needed to make sure that the school nurse was there to take care of my child. I was told at that time that they would make sure that JT was taken care of on the field trip and that he would have a "1-on-1". I admit that I was completely skeptical of this and I sent JT on his field trip with my Blackberry programmed as to when he was to check his blood sugar, and eat. I was not going to take any chances on the student teacher assigned to him putting him in any danger. Later that week I went to the school for a party in JT's class, to help the teacher figure out how many carbs JT had consumed and calculate his insulin dosage for his insulin pump. At that time I was told by the school nurse "it's not in my contract to take care of a child on an insulin pump". At that moment, I realized that there was a complete disregard for my childs well being. I found out the next day that his A1C (a fancy blood test that gives you an average of what your blood sugars are daily, the lower the A1C the better you have control of your blood sugar 6 is average) was a 9.2. Up 2 whole points since the beginning of the school year. I called the superintendents office and spoke with Dr. Nolte, the assistant, and informed him that my child would not return to school until the staff was trained properly! I was not going to subject my child to a life filled with severe complications because the people who are charged with taking care of him everyday are not doing just that. I also at that time asked for a 504 plan. I was told that he did not qualify for a 504 plan because he did not have any mental handicaps. I still insisted on having one. I also spoke with the principal and told him that he needed to correct this immediately. In January there was a collaborative meeting put in place, where Dr. Nolte informed the school nurse that he wanted a step-by-step care plan in place for JT... He wanted to know exactly who was doing what, and when, and what to do if that person was not available. My husband and I were pleased. We felt as if the school was really going to work with us on this. Jt was absent the entire month of January (with the exception of 4 days) because of the school not furnishing the revised care plan. Once I received it I reviewed it and made notes as to what was wrong with it. and spoke with the school nurse to explain to her that this "new" plan was the same thing that was already in place. And I would not sign it. The school social worker was then sent to my house to try and coerce me to sign it. My husband clearly stated that neither of us would sign that form. Yesterday the social worker returned to my house with a Waynesville Police officer with the forms again. I was at a private school enrolling JT at this time, because my husband and I had decided that we had had enough of trying to work with Haywood County Public School. Jt's A1C this month was down to an 8.1... I was able to prove my point that him being in a situation where they did not know how to take care of him, was detrimental to his health. Today, this morning, the school social worker again came to my house with letters from the school principal stating that I would be charged with Medical Neglect for not signing the care plan. And that by me keeping him out of school I would be charged with academic neglect for all 3 of my children. As of this morning at 10am, none of my children are enrolled in Haywood County Public Schools, because of this. This is insane that a principal would go to such great lengths to not take care of a child. All I have asked for is for them to treat him according to his doctors orders. and this is impossible for them to do. I asked for a 504 plan on 2 separate occasions, and I was denied. Parent to parent, I am asking you to please intervene and make this right. It is not fair for my children to have to leave all of their friends because of 1 school refusing to step up to the plate and do what they are required by federal law to do. Thank you so much for your time and prompt attention to this matter, Amber Fuller

